        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-24">April 24,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received April 23—5:24 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>848. Embassy informed Communist troops began entering city by Northwest gate at
                    approximately 5 a. m. 24th. Desultory shots exchanged during night in streets
                    between emergency police force and marauders have virtually ceased. No disorders
                    in neighborhood Embassy compounds. No American nationals have applied to Embassy
                    for permission move [into] Chancery compound, despite notice circulated 23d.
                    Embassy personnel and offices secure.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 848, repeated Shanghai 434, American Embassy Canton 294.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
